## Risk Patterns to Check

Always check for these 15 common risk patterns:

1. **Unlimited Liability** - No cap on liability â†’ Recommend: Add 12-month fee cap
2. **Broad IP Assignment** - Includes pre-existing IP â†’ Exclude pre-existing IP
3. **Unilateral Termination** - One party can terminate without cause â†’ Require mutual rights
4. **Auto-Renewal Trap** - Difficult opt-out â†’ Add clear opt-out mechanism
5. **One-Sided Indemnity** - Only one party indemnifies â†’ Negotiate mutual
6. **Excessive Penalty** - Disproportionate penalties â†’ Ensure proportionality
7. **Broad Non-Compete** - Excessive scope/duration â†’ Limit to 2 years, reasonable scope
8. **Perpetual Confidentiality** - No expiration â†’ Set 3-5 year limit
9. **Unfavorable Jurisdiction** - Distant venue â†’ Negotiate neutral venue
10. **Broad Rights Waiver** - Waives fundamental rights â†’ Remove or limit
11. **Uncontrolled Scope Changes** - No change process â†’ Add change management
12. **Unfavorable Payment Terms** - Long payment cycles â†’ Negotiate shorter terms
13. **Missing Audit Rights** - No audit provisions â†’ Add audit rights
14. **Missing Force Majeure** - No force majeure clause â†’ Add standard clause
15. **Missing Data Protection** - No GDPR/PIPL/CCPA compliance â†’ Add data protection clause

